{"id": 231979560, "title": "AG CAN\u2019T BE ATTACKED IN THIS MANNER - CSC ON PM'S STATEMENT", "text": "In a statement issued yesterday, Mamba said the comments by Prime Minister Russell Mmiso Dlamini were \u2018very\u2019 unfortunate and that an attack on the Office of the AG was similar to an attack on accountability. The chairman explained that the Constitution of Swaziland, 2005 accorded the AG and other holders of constitutional office the status of a superior court of judges. \u201cTherefore, there are procedures to be followed in raising concerns. Section 207 (2) of the Constitution states how the AG is appointed. Section 207 (7) talks about the independence of the office. This is to ensure that he executes his duties with independence and without fear and or intimidation. Subsection 9 states that where the AG has misconducted himself, it is the Civil Service Commission that will deal with the matter,\u201d Mamba said.", "summary": "MBABANE &ndash; The Chairman of the Civil Service Commission (CSC), Simanga Mamba, has said that the Auditor General (AG) cannot be attacked in the manner", "url": "http://www.times.co.sz/news/145530-ag-can%E2%80%99t-be-attacked-in-this-manner-csc-on-pm-s-statement.html", "image": null, "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-09 13:39:34", "author": "Prime Minister Russell", "authors": ["Prime Minister Russell"], "language": "en", "source_country": "sz", "sentiment": -0.345}